WEBVTT

00:13.979 --> 00:15.248
[SIGHING]

00:16.015 --> 00:17.684
Last night was fun.

00:17.717 --> 00:19.085
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

00:19.118 --> 00:21.354
We've gotta do that
more often.

00:19.118 --> 00:21.354
[CHUCKLES]

00:21.387 --> 00:23.156
Definitely.

00:24.724 --> 00:27.860
You don't think
the kids heard us,
do you?

00:27.893 --> 00:30.530
Well, they didn't
hear me.

00:30.563 --> 00:33.266
Oh, stop it.
[GIGGLES]

00:30.563 --> 00:33.266
[CHUCKLES]

00:36.002 --> 00:37.136
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

00:37.169 --> 00:38.371
Hey, Sam, good...

00:40.907 --> 00:41.941
Where is she?

00:41.974 --> 00:42.975
[KIDS SCREAMING]

00:43.009 --> 00:44.076
Hey, Anthony.

00:44.109 --> 00:46.045
Have you seen
your sister?

00:46.078 --> 00:48.948
Not since yesterday,
when I got home from camp.

00:48.981 --> 00:50.350
Can you make me waffles?

00:50.383 --> 00:52.519
Not the frozen kind,
the ones you make
from scratch.

00:54.487 --> 00:55.588
[LINE RINGING]

00:57.123 --> 00:58.291
SAM: [ON VOICEMAIL]
<i>Hey, it's Sam, leave a message.</i>

00:58.324 --> 00:59.391
[SIGHS IN EXASPERATION]

00:59.425 --> 01:00.860
It still keeps
going to her voicemail.

01:00.893 --> 01:02.361
Robby's not picking
up either.

01:02.395 --> 01:05.164
You think
they're together?

01:02.395 --> 01:05.164
Well, they are teenagers

01:05.197 --> 01:07.567
who have been
living together
all summer.

01:07.600 --> 01:10.970
No way, I'm not ready
to go there. You know, I...

01:11.003 --> 01:12.872
Trusted Robby.
Sam better be okay.

01:12.905 --> 01:13.773
[NOTIFICATION CHIMES]

01:17.577 --> 01:18.578
Ugh.

01:18.611 --> 01:20.146
You need a password.

01:21.614 --> 01:23.216
[UNLOCK CHIMES]

01:23.249 --> 01:26.252
What? Don't look at me
like that. Now is not the time.

01:29.188 --> 01:30.723
Why would she ask
if she's okay?

01:33.192 --> 01:35.161
She was drinking?

01:36.162 --> 01:37.464
"The cops"?

01:38.965 --> 01:40.466
What are you doing?

01:40.500 --> 01:42.035
I should have thought
of this sooner.

01:42.068 --> 01:43.603
Find my iPhone.

01:45.171 --> 01:46.772
Here it is.

01:46.806 --> 01:49.876
She's somewhere between
Sherman Way and Saticoy?

01:49.909 --> 01:51.744
Well, what is she doing
in Reseda?

02:26.078 --> 02:27.614
[PHONE RINGING]

02:32.051 --> 02:35.020
Another new update?
I just got this.

02:35.054 --> 02:36.289
ROBBY: Hey.

02:40.359 --> 02:43.796
Thanks for letting us
crash here last night.

02:44.264 --> 02:45.598
It's no problem.

02:45.632 --> 02:48.334
But, look, I'm gonna have
to tell LaRusso about this.

02:48.367 --> 02:50.436
It's his kid.

02:48.367 --> 02:50.436
Look, please don't.

02:50.469 --> 02:52.839
If he sees her like this,
it'll crush him.

02:52.872 --> 02:54.374
Let me take the blame.

02:54.407 --> 02:57.410
I'll say I got drunk and
told Sam to bring me here.

03:06.118 --> 03:08.354
Should be right here.

03:13.192 --> 03:14.594
What the hell?

03:17.062 --> 03:18.264
Johnny?

03:18.964 --> 03:20.199
Oh, no.

03:20.233 --> 03:21.433
DANIEL: Johnny, come on,
I saw your car outside.

03:21.467 --> 03:23.469
I know you're
in there, open up.

03:23.502 --> 03:26.072
All right, go in
the other room,
I got your back.

03:26.105 --> 03:27.373
DANIEL: Johnny!

03:29.375 --> 03:31.778
Hey, man.

03:29.375 --> 03:31.778
Is my daughter here?

03:31.811 --> 03:32.879
Yeah, just calm down.

03:32.912 --> 03:34.747
Don't tell me
to calm down, all right?
Where is she?

03:34.781 --> 03:37.417
Look, they had
a crazy night.
Kids do these things.

03:37.450 --> 03:38.718
Just don't overreact.

03:38.751 --> 03:40.619
Okay. Who the hell are you
to tell me about parenting?

03:40.653 --> 03:42.588
You need to open
this door right now.

03:42.621 --> 03:44.423
Hey!

03:42.621 --> 03:44.423
I don't need
to do anything

03:44.457 --> 03:46.259
until you cool off.

03:49.027 --> 03:50.230
[GRUNTS]

03:51.998 --> 03:54.367
Sam!

03:51.998 --> 03:54.367
JOHNNY: What the hell
is wrong with you?

03:55.968 --> 03:56.836
[GRUNTS]

04:00.673 --> 04:01.674
Fight!

04:03.943 --> 04:05.245
[BOTH GRUNTING]

04:09.248 --> 04:10.483
[GROANS]

04:11.717 --> 04:12.585
[GRUNTS]

04:16.188 --> 04:17.724
What is going on out there?

04:21.026 --> 04:22.995
You wanna finish this?

04:23.028 --> 04:24.297
Bring it on.

04:26.065 --> 04:28.067
Dad, stop!

04:26.065 --> 04:28.067
ROBBY: Don't!

04:28.100 --> 04:30.335
Sam. What happened?
Are you okay?

04:30.369 --> 04:31.504
[STAMMERING] Yeah, I'm fine.

04:31.537 --> 04:33.239
Why didn't you
call or text us?

04:33.272 --> 04:34.873
Mr. LaRusso,
it was my fault.

04:34.907 --> 04:35.842
I brought her here.

04:35.875 --> 04:37.243
Wait, now, don't even start.

04:37.276 --> 04:39.211
I gave you
a second chance.

04:39.244 --> 04:41.413
This whole thing
was a mistake.

04:41.447 --> 04:43.516
You know, you wanna end up
like him, that's up to you.

04:43.549 --> 04:45.551
All right,
come on, Sam.

04:43.549 --> 04:45.551
Please, Dad.

04:45.584 --> 04:47.687
Sam, I don't wanna
hear it. Let's go.

05:02.100 --> 05:06.138
<i> [CRUEL SUMMER</i> PLAYING]

05:06.171 --> 05:12.177
<i>♪ Hot summer streets
and the pavements are burning
I sit around</i>

05:12.211 --> 05:14.980
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

05:15.014 --> 05:20.053
<i>♪ Trying to smile
but the air is so heavy and dry</i>

05:24.590 --> 05:28.995
<i> ♪ Strange voices are saying
what did they say?</i>

05:30.696 --> 05:32.965
Still nothing
from Tory?

05:32.999 --> 05:36.035
No, what about you?

05:32.999 --> 05:36.035
She won't text me back.

05:36.068 --> 05:37.402
I'm getting
kind of worried.

05:37.436 --> 05:39.539
I couldn't even
find her after
the party.

05:39.572 --> 05:42.274
You think she got
in trouble with the cops?

05:39.572 --> 05:42.274
I don't know.

05:42.308 --> 05:45.478
But missing the
first day of school
is not a good sign.

05:45.744 --> 05:47.145
Yeah.

05:47.179 --> 05:53.453
<i> ♪ Leaving me here on my own
It's a cruel, cruel summer ♪</i>

05:55.654 --> 05:57.489
You had to pull up
right in front?

05:57.522 --> 05:58.791
If you wanted to drive
your own car today,

05:58.824 --> 06:00.093
you wouldn't have
done what you did.

06:00.126 --> 06:03.762
Dad. How many times
do I have to
tell you I'm sorry?

06:03.795 --> 06:06.965
I made a mistake.

06:03.795 --> 06:06.965
Everyone makes mistakes.

06:06.999 --> 06:09.735
But when you get
in trouble,
you come to me or your mom.

06:09.769 --> 06:11.437
Not that guy.

06:11.470 --> 06:14.106
I'm sorry I didn't
come to you and Mom.

06:14.139 --> 06:16.676
That was my fault,
not Robby's.

06:17.977 --> 06:19.612
I thought I could help him.

06:19.645 --> 06:22.882
But he's got
his own family.
I need to focus on mine.

06:22.915 --> 06:27.520
Just do me a favor, okay?
This year, just concentrate
on precalculus, okay?

06:35.060 --> 06:35.928
[DOOR CLOSES]

06:36.862 --> 06:39.799
Got you some pencils
and some paper.

06:39.832 --> 06:41.401
I wasn't sure
what you needed.

06:42.134 --> 06:43.536
Thanks.

06:43.569 --> 06:45.605
Couldn't find
a Trapper Keeper,
are those still cool?

06:47.105 --> 06:48.107
I don't know
what that is.

06:48.140 --> 06:50.943
Ah, I had one with
a fighter jet,
it was awesome.

06:53.979 --> 06:56.549
You okay? You nervous
about your first day?

06:57.149 --> 06:58.618
No, but...

06:59.651 --> 07:02.121
Just feel bad about Sam
and the LaRussos.

07:03.121 --> 07:04.423
[SIGHS]

07:04.456 --> 07:07.726
I know you don't wanna hear it,
but Mr. LaRusso was good to me.

07:07.759 --> 07:10.028
Miyagi-Do Karate
helped me out a lot.

07:10.062 --> 07:11.197
[PHONE RINGING]

07:15.867 --> 07:17.303
Look...

07:17.336 --> 07:20.840
All I'm saying is, maybe you
guys can learn a thing or two
from each other.

07:22.708 --> 07:24.643
All right, you better go.

07:24.677 --> 07:26.612
Thanks for driving me, Dad.

07:34.587 --> 07:38.157
JOHNNY: [ON VOICEMAIL]
<i>You've reached the smartphone
of Johnny Lawrence,</i>

07:38.190 --> 07:39.959
<i> sensei of Cobra Kai Karate.</i>

07:39.992 --> 07:41.026
<i> Please leave a message,</i>

07:41.060 --> 07:43.596
<i> and I'll get back to you
when I get a chance.</i>

07:43.629 --> 07:45.598
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

07:46.298 --> 07:47.867
Excuse me?

07:47.900 --> 07:51.537
I'm new to this school,
can you help me find
Ms. Santino's class?

07:52.037 --> 07:53.072
Hey.

07:54.840 --> 07:56.075
Wow.

07:56.108 --> 07:57.143
It's that bad, huh?

07:58.277 --> 08:00.446
I feel like an idiot.

08:00.479 --> 08:02.180
We should've just
gone to my house

08:02.214 --> 08:03.983
and been honest
with my parents.

08:05.985 --> 08:07.053
I'm sorry.

08:07.719 --> 08:09.589
No, it's my fault, too.

08:13.392 --> 08:15.962
From now on, no more lying.

08:20.232 --> 08:21.501
I have to tell you something.

08:26.438 --> 08:28.707
Miguel gave me
the Medal of Honor.

08:28.741 --> 08:32.278
And I put it in the backyard
so someone would find it.

08:33.345 --> 08:34.647
Why would you do that?

08:35.781 --> 08:37.917
I didn't want him
to earn any points
with you.

08:38.684 --> 08:40.753
And we'd just kissed and...

08:44.623 --> 08:46.192
I guess I felt insecure.

08:48.794 --> 08:53.198
Thank you.
For telling me
the truth.

08:53.232 --> 08:55.902
Well, it feels better
to get that off my chest.

09:01.340 --> 09:02.575
Robby...

09:01.340 --> 09:02.575
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

09:04.844 --> 09:07.547
Well, I can't be
late on my first day.

09:10.549 --> 09:11.817
See you later.

09:17.422 --> 09:19.057
Good morning, students
and faculty,

09:19.091 --> 09:22.728
welcome to a brand-new year
at West Valley High.

09:22.761 --> 09:24.763
[ON SPEAKER]
<i> I hope you all had a
wonderful summer</i>

09:24.796 --> 09:26.699
<i> and are ready to dive
back into the school year.</i>

09:26.732 --> 09:28.801
Dude, you kissed Sam?

09:26.732 --> 09:28.801
Yeah.

09:28.834 --> 09:32.004
Nice.

09:28.834 --> 09:32.004
No, not nice.

09:32.037 --> 09:33.939
I shouldn't have
done that to Tory.

09:33.973 --> 09:35.875
Why limit yourself
to one chick?

09:36.742 --> 09:38.310
I'm planning on
having a full rotation

09:38.344 --> 09:39.678
by the time
we get to midterms.

09:39.711 --> 09:41.413
What?

09:39.711 --> 09:41.413
STUDENT: Hey, man.

09:41.447 --> 09:44.984
Just wanted to say,
I wet the bed
till I was 13...

09:45.784 --> 09:48.287
There's nothing
to be ashamed of.

09:48.320 --> 09:49.721
Get the hell out
of my face!

09:49.755 --> 09:51.223
[STUDENTS LAUGHING]

09:51.257 --> 09:53.659
What's that guy's problem?

09:51.257 --> 09:53.659
I don't know.

09:53.692 --> 09:56.395
WOMAN: [ON SPEAKER]
<i> You can also purchase tickets
for the fall musical,</i>

09:56.428 --> 09:59.197
<i> which will be a production
of the global hit</i> Grease.

09:59.231 --> 10:02.068
I do appreciate
your passion taking
initiative and all,

10:02.101 --> 10:04.804
but this is highly
unusual timing.

10:04.837 --> 10:07.206
And your resume's
a little spotty.

10:07.239 --> 10:11.610
I mean, do you have
any actual security guard
experience? Mr...

10:11.644 --> 10:14.313
Oh, Stingray.
Just one word, Stingray.

10:14.846 --> 10:15.814
Hmm.

10:15.848 --> 10:19.318
I don't have any actual
experience, per se.

10:19.351 --> 10:21.053
But I just recently won

10:21.086 --> 10:24.289
the Black versus Red Challenge
at Coyote Creek.

10:24.322 --> 10:25.524
No big deal.

10:24.322 --> 10:25.524
Hmm.

10:25.557 --> 10:28.293
Except for
the karate community,
it's a very big deal.

10:28.327 --> 10:30.829
My sensei's been very
pleased with my progress.

10:30.863 --> 10:33.966
And I think, in time,
you will see a yellow belt

10:33.999 --> 10:36.802
strapped around
my midsection.

10:33.999 --> 10:36.802
I see.

10:36.835 --> 10:40.205
This is a very nice setup
you have here, by the way.

10:40.239 --> 10:41.806
It's, uh... It's terrific.

10:41.840 --> 10:44.877
My question for you is...

10:44.910 --> 10:49.181
What is the teachers' lounge
situation looking like?

10:49.214 --> 10:52.317
WOMAN: [ON SPEAKER]
<i>And finally as we embark upon
another academic year,</i>

10:52.350 --> 10:55.287
<i> it's important to remember
to be tolerant and accepting</i>

10:55.320 --> 10:57.789
of all of our peers,
regardless of...

10:55.320 --> 10:57.789
[DOOR OPENS]

10:57.822 --> 11:00.826
<i> Hey, you're not supposed
to be in here.</i>

11:00.859 --> 11:02.294
<i> I don't care, move!</i>

11:02.327 --> 11:03.562
[RADIO FREQUENCY SCREECHING]

11:03.596 --> 11:05.297
<i> Give that back! Ow!</i>

11:03.596 --> 11:05.297
[SCOFFS]

11:07.266 --> 11:08.801
You're not allowed to...

11:10.635 --> 11:12.505
Samantha LaRusso.

11:12.538 --> 11:15.608
[ON SPEAKER]<i> I know
what you did and now
you're gonna pay for it.</i>

11:15.641 --> 11:17.143
[STUDENTS EXCLAIMING]

11:18.544 --> 11:20.813
I'm coming for you, bitch!

11:20.846 --> 11:22.214
[STUDENTS EXCLAIMING]

11:22.247 --> 11:23.281
[SCHOOL BELL RINGING]

11:23.315 --> 11:24.984
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

12:04.623 --> 12:06.325
I saw what you did
at the party.

12:07.859 --> 12:09.228
You kissed Miguel.

12:09.261 --> 12:10.763
[STUDENTS EXCLAIM]

12:12.631 --> 12:13.833
I...

12:15.567 --> 12:16.769
I...

12:17.736 --> 12:18.804
[GRUNTS]

12:22.707 --> 12:24.343
Get back in there!

12:24.376 --> 12:25.845
[BOTH GROANING]

12:29.714 --> 12:30.983
[SAM GROANS]

12:34.153 --> 12:35.154
[CROWD CHEERING]

12:36.388 --> 12:37.555
STUDENT: Yeah, get her!

12:37.589 --> 12:38.991
[GRUNTING]

12:40.526 --> 12:41.393
You okay?

12:42.294 --> 12:43.295
Stop!

12:44.496 --> 12:45.397
STUDENT: Let her go!

12:46.966 --> 12:48.099
Hey!

12:48.133 --> 12:50.336
ROBBY: Settle down! I'm sure
we can figure this out...

12:50.802 --> 12:52.070
[STUDENTS GASP]

12:52.103 --> 12:54.506
Hey, man, we gotta
do something.

12:52.103 --> 12:54.506
Good idea.

12:54.539 --> 12:56.575
I'm gonna get a teacher.

12:56.608 --> 12:58.043
[STUDENTS EXCLAIM]

12:58.810 --> 13:00.612
Oh, it is on!

13:00.646 --> 13:02.148
[STUDENTS SCREAMING]

13:03.081 --> 13:04.116
[GROANS]

13:08.020 --> 13:09.855
Yeah!

13:14.326 --> 13:15.594
I'm not gonna
throw the first punch.

13:15.627 --> 13:16.962
Too bad.

13:17.695 --> 13:18.564
[GRUNTS]

13:21.033 --> 13:21.901
[GROANS]

13:23.034 --> 13:24.436
You're going down, nerd.

13:24.470 --> 13:25.771
Come and get it, dickhead.

13:25.804 --> 13:27.206
[BOTH GRUNTING]

13:31.343 --> 13:32.311
[BOTH SCREAMING]

13:33.379 --> 13:36.181
Stop fighting! Stop!

13:36.214 --> 13:38.650
Oh, you want
some of this? [GRUNTS]

13:38.684 --> 13:40.152
[GROANING]

13:42.287 --> 13:45.223
Come on, guys,
can't we all just
get along?

13:45.257 --> 13:46.125
[SCREAMS]

13:47.826 --> 13:48.894
[GRUNTING]

14:24.496 --> 14:25.865
[BOTH GRUNTING]

14:35.240 --> 14:36.275
[SCREAMING]

14:39.811 --> 14:41.046
This is out of control!

14:41.080 --> 14:42.981
Get me security in the
main corridor, right away!

14:43.014 --> 14:44.916
It's okay, sir, I got this.

14:44.950 --> 14:46.485
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

14:53.558 --> 14:54.927
Yeah.

14:56.661 --> 14:57.529
[GROANS]

14:58.764 --> 15:00.532
[STUDENTS GASP]

15:00.566 --> 15:02.368
[ALL SHOUTING]

15:08.506 --> 15:09.675
[GRUNTING]

15:17.515 --> 15:18.717
[PANTING]

15:18.750 --> 15:20.251
Can't you just
stop it already?

15:20.285 --> 15:22.421
What's the matter?
You can't keep up?

15:23.288 --> 15:24.290
[GRUNTS]

15:25.257 --> 15:26.592
[GRUNTING]

15:27.926 --> 15:29.094
[SCREAMS]

15:34.365 --> 15:36.568
You have to
do something,
Mr. Palmer.

15:39.571 --> 15:41.507
Hey! Break it up!

15:45.110 --> 15:47.545
Screw this, they don't
pay me enough.

15:47.579 --> 15:49.114
[ALL GRUNTING]

15:50.482 --> 15:51.483
Not again.

15:53.251 --> 15:54.119
[GROANS]

15:54.153 --> 15:55.887
You can't cheat
your way
out of this one.

15:55.921 --> 15:57.156
[BOTH GRUNTING]

15:57.189 --> 15:59.424
Like that move?
I learned it
from your dad.

15:59.457 --> 16:00.558
[GRUNTS]

16:00.592 --> 16:01.593
[GIRL SCREAMS]

16:10.669 --> 16:12.504
[BOTH GRUNTING]

16:12.537 --> 16:13.672
[GIRL SCREAMING]

16:15.907 --> 16:17.076
[GRUNTS]

16:22.748 --> 16:23.716
[STUDENTS GASP]

16:24.716 --> 16:25.951
Should've stayed
in Cobra Kai.

16:25.984 --> 16:28.153
You could have been a badass.

16:29.954 --> 16:31.323
[GRUNTS]

16:33.091 --> 16:34.493
Who's badass now?

16:38.397 --> 16:42.500
Demetri, I know you're in here.

16:42.534 --> 16:45.104
Figured you'd hide in the
computer lab. You damn nerd.

16:52.911 --> 16:54.346
I'm coming for you.

17:06.358 --> 17:07.258
[GASPS]

17:07.292 --> 17:08.160
Boo.

17:09.694 --> 17:12.431
DEMETRI: Shit, shit, shit!

17:09.694 --> 17:12.431
Come here, Demetri!

17:13.866 --> 17:15.434
[BOTH GRUNTING]

17:19.638 --> 17:20.773
Tory, enough!

17:21.606 --> 17:22.574
What?

17:28.613 --> 17:29.581
[GROANS]

17:35.620 --> 17:36.755
ROBBY: Sam!

17:36.788 --> 17:38.057
[GRUNTS]

17:43.662 --> 17:45.330
Oh, now you're in trouble.

17:50.035 --> 17:51.803
Get off me... [GRUNTS]

17:51.837 --> 17:55.707
Hey, hey! Come on! Come on.

17:55.740 --> 17:59.311
No, come on.
You guys are done.

17:55.740 --> 17:59.311
Let me at him. Come on.

18:01.079 --> 18:02.347
[BOTH GRUNTING]

18:02.914 --> 18:04.116
[SCREAMING]

18:12.958 --> 18:14.159
[GRUNTING]

18:21.099 --> 18:22.800
Is that the only way
you know
how to fight?

18:22.834 --> 18:24.136
Dirty?

18:24.936 --> 18:26.638
This isn't a tournament.

18:28.040 --> 18:29.341
There are no rules.

18:33.145 --> 18:35.180
[GRUNTING]

18:43.254 --> 18:44.456
No hard feelings.

18:52.163 --> 18:54.399
Sorry, Eli.

18:54.967 --> 18:56.502
[BOTH GRUNTING]

19:03.608 --> 19:05.443
That's for taking
advantage of Sam.

19:05.477 --> 19:07.346
I would never.

19:05.477 --> 19:07.346
Then why did it happen?

19:13.018 --> 19:14.753
[BOTH GRUNTING]

19:20.591 --> 19:21.627
[GROANS]

19:24.630 --> 19:25.764
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

19:26.198 --> 19:27.633
No mercy.

19:29.834 --> 19:30.836
[GRUNTS]

19:36.207 --> 19:38.177
[PANTING]

19:41.446 --> 19:43.215
[GRUNTING]

19:49.988 --> 19:51.890
She doesn't love you.
She loves me!

19:51.923 --> 19:52.791
[GRUNTS]

20:15.980 --> 20:19.017
I wasn't taught
the difference between
mercy and honor,

20:19.050 --> 20:20.752
and I payed
the price for it.

20:20.786 --> 20:22.253
If I'm extra hard on you,

20:22.286 --> 20:25.890
it's only because
you have the potential
to be better than I ever was.

20:25.924 --> 20:27.359
You want that, don't you?

20:30.662 --> 20:31.964
[MUFFLED SHOUTING]

20:38.537 --> 20:39.571
I'm sorry.

20:40.906 --> 20:41.907
[SCREAMING]

20:42.407 --> 20:43.609
[STUDENTS CHEERING]

20:48.213 --> 20:49.348
Miguel!

20:55.253 --> 20:56.688
[STUDENTS GASP]

20:58.490 --> 21:00.525
OFFICER: Clear the way,
clear the way.

21:01.726 --> 21:03.495
We need an ambulance
at West Valley High.

21:04.829 --> 21:06.398
Robby, what did you do?

22:03.755 --> 22:04.790
AMANDA: Daniel!

22:06.591 --> 22:09.428
I just got a call
from the high school.

22:06.591 --> 22:09.428
What's wrong?

22:15.100 --> 22:16.934
[PHONE RINGING]

22:16.968 --> 22:18.804
Ah, how do I change that?

22:21.907 --> 22:24.443
Stupid smart phone.

22:24.476 --> 22:25.711
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

22:27.745 --> 22:29.514
Carmen?

22:33.618 --> 22:35.520
DOCTOR: You've seen your
fair share of these.

22:35.554 --> 22:38.623
So you know
the next 24 hours
are critical.

22:39.657 --> 22:41.360
But he's gonna
pull through, right?

22:42.627 --> 22:44.129
DOCTOR:<i> We're doing
everything we can.</i>

22:46.031 --> 22:47.432
Excuse me.

22:49.334 --> 22:50.535
[SOBBING]

22:57.175 --> 22:58.577
I'm so sorry.

22:59.110 --> 23:00.612
Sorry?

23:00.945 --> 23:02.080
Sorry?

23:03.347 --> 23:06.485
Before Miguel met you,
he was a sweet boy.

23:07.018 --> 23:09.020
He avoided fights.

23:09.054 --> 23:11.490
Now look what you did.

23:09.054 --> 23:11.490
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

23:13.424 --> 23:15.961
I never want to
see you again.

23:28.305 --> 23:29.340
It's all right now,
okay?

23:29.374 --> 23:30.675
Everything's gonna
be all right.

23:30.708 --> 23:33.178
I'm gonna make sure
this girl gets expelled.

23:33.211 --> 23:35.213
[SOBBING] I don't
care about Tory.

23:35.246 --> 23:37.081
I just want Miguel to be okay.

23:37.114 --> 23:37.949
[WEEPING]

23:37.982 --> 23:39.985
I can't believe
Robby would do that.

23:40.785 --> 23:43.421
It's all my fault.

23:40.785 --> 23:43.421
No, no.

23:43.454 --> 23:44.990
No, don't say that, Sam.

23:45.790 --> 23:46.925
[SOBBING]

23:49.127 --> 23:50.095
[PHONE CHIMES]

23:57.836 --> 23:59.371
MIGUEL: [ON VOICEMAIL]
<i> Hey, Sensei, it's Miguel,</i>

23:59.404 --> 24:01.238
<i> I knocked on
your door this morning,</i>

24:01.272 --> 24:03.607
<i> but I guess you already left.</i>

24:03.641 --> 24:05.743
<i> I'm having some
girl trouble and, well,</i>

24:05.777 --> 24:08.513
<i> you're better at this
sort of thing than me.</i>

24:08.546 --> 24:10.782
<i> I'll come by the dojo
after school.</i>

24:10.815 --> 24:12.349
<i> My mom is working tonight,</i>

24:12.383 --> 24:14.986
<i> so maybe we
could grab a burger
at that place you like?</i>

24:15.020 --> 24:16.855
<i> I'll talk to you later.</i>

24:15.020 --> 24:16.855
[SOBBING]

24:39.343 --> 24:40.579
[SIGHS]

24:47.986 --> 24:49.020
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

25:04.302 --> 25:05.504
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

25:44.209 --> 25:45.644
[BELL CHIMING]

25:53.117 --> 25:56.054
[PEOPLE CHANTING]

26:14.072 --> 26:15.607
[STUDENTS CHANTING]

26:16.541 --> 26:17.842
Class.

26:19.076 --> 26:20.145
We have a visitor.

26:21.546 --> 26:22.814
What the hell
do you think
you're doing?

26:22.847 --> 26:25.483
What does it look like?
I'm teaching my students.

26:25.516 --> 26:27.585
Your students?

26:27.619 --> 26:30.121
You let them down when
they needed you the most.

26:31.355 --> 26:34.259
Somebody needed
to remind them
what it takes to win.

26:40.331 --> 26:41.833
[SCOFFS]

26:41.866 --> 26:43.634
After everything
I did for you?

26:43.667 --> 26:45.704
Miguel's in the hospital
because of you.

26:45.737 --> 26:47.505
He showed mercy
to Robby Keene
because of you.

26:47.538 --> 26:50.642
If he dies,
that's on you.

26:52.443 --> 26:54.112
JOHN: I did warn you
about this.

26:55.747 --> 26:58.016
I told you
not to show weakness.

27:00.184 --> 27:01.219
Get out.

27:01.252 --> 27:02.787
This is my dojo.

27:04.622 --> 27:06.157
Oh, I forgot to tell you,

27:07.325 --> 27:08.893
when you were out of town,

27:08.927 --> 27:11.062
I had a little talk
with the landlord.

27:12.163 --> 27:15.333
It turns out he doesn't
like you much.

27:15.366 --> 27:19.671
But you know the problem
with those handshake deals,

27:21.239 --> 27:23.108
there are no guarantees.

27:25.810 --> 27:27.212
You can't do this.

27:30.615 --> 27:32.050
Of course I can.

27:34.119 --> 27:35.887
I founded Cobra Kai.

27:38.089 --> 27:39.658
It belongs to me.

27:40.725 --> 27:42.360
It always has,

27:44.462 --> 27:46.331
and it always will.

27:50.168 --> 27:52.871
I will never
let my students lose.

27:58.643 --> 28:00.979
Even if they have
to learn the hard way.

28:07.751 --> 28:10.154
One day you will
thank me for this, Johnny.

28:10.187 --> 28:11.222
[SCOFFS]

28:16.661 --> 28:18.430
This was a mistake.

28:22.733 --> 28:24.769
You want Cobra Kai...

28:27.038 --> 28:28.206
It's yours.

28:36.447 --> 28:37.782
JOHN: Class...

28:39.350 --> 28:40.851
Forward strike.

28:40.885 --> 28:42.153
[SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE]

28:43.787 --> 28:46.357
[STUDENTS CHANTING
IN OTHER LANGUAGE]

28:55.699 --> 28:56.967
Hey, where is she?

28:57.001 --> 28:59.103
I got her her favorite sandwich
from il Tramezzino.

28:59.136 --> 29:01.305
Still waiting for her
to get back from her X-rays.

29:01.339 --> 29:03.674
Now the doctor thinks
she might have
cracked a rib.

29:03.707 --> 29:05.944
Oh, God.

29:06.844 --> 29:08.145
This has to stop, Daniel.

29:08.179 --> 29:11.382
I know, you're right.
I know, I swear. I...

29:11.415 --> 29:13.585
I'm not gonna let Cobra Kai
get away with this...

29:13.618 --> 29:16.954
Enough with Cobra Kai.

29:16.987 --> 29:20.057
Don't you see
what this stupid
rivalry has done?

29:20.091 --> 29:21.826
Our daughter
is in the hospital.

29:22.593 --> 29:23.795
No more karate.

29:23.828 --> 29:26.498
Fine. Okay. All right.
Amanda, I know you're right.

29:26.531 --> 29:28.266
No more karate.

29:29.067 --> 29:30.068
It's over.

29:38.376 --> 29:40.512
<i> [CRUEL SUMMER</i> PLAYING]

29:44.448 --> 29:50.388
<i>♪ Hot summer streets
and the pavements are burning</i>

29:50.421 --> 29:52.823
<i> ♪ I sit around</i>

29:52.857 --> 29:56.360
I wore this when I was training
for my first tournament
back in '81.

29:56.394 --> 29:57.495
I want you to have it.

29:57.529 --> 30:03.334
<i>♪ Trying to smile
but the air is so heavy and dry</i>

30:03.367 --> 30:04.935
[MIGUEL SCREAMING]

30:04.969 --> 30:07.071
Who's the man?

30:04.969 --> 30:07.071
Tell me you're the man.

30:07.105 --> 30:10.307
I'm the man. It's Cobra Kai.

30:10.341 --> 30:11.509
Never accept defeat.

30:12.309 --> 30:15.279
<i> ♪ Cruel summer</i>

30:15.312 --> 30:18.149
One of the best things in my
life has been teaching you.

30:18.183 --> 30:22.520
I'll always be on your side
and always have your
best interest at heart.

30:22.553 --> 30:28.059
<i> ♪ It's a cruel, cruel summer</i>

30:28.092 --> 30:30.261
<i> ♪ Now you're gone</i>

30:36.400 --> 30:39.437
I tried my best. I thought
I was doing the right thing.

30:41.472 --> 30:42.439
I'm sorry.

30:42.473 --> 30:47.712
<i> ♪ The city is crowded
my friends are away</i>

30:47.745 --> 30:51.049
<i> ♪ And I'm on my own</i>

30:55.653 --> 30:58.089
Don't worry.
Miguel is a good kid.

30:58.722 --> 31:00.191
I won't let him go astray.

31:03.561 --> 31:09.634
<i> ♪ It's a cruel, cruel summer</i>

31:11.535 --> 31:13.004
[GLASS SHATTERING]

31:14.905 --> 31:16.541
[PHONE RINGING]

31:18.542 --> 31:19.544
[GRUNTS]

31:25.550 --> 31:29.186
<i> ♪ Leaving me here on my own</i>

31:29.219 --> 31:35.026
<i> ♪ It's a cruel
cruel summer... ♪</i>

31:36.894 --> 31:39.097
[PHONE RINGING]
